There is something magnificent about them. With their deep brown eyes fringed with seemingly endless lashes, lilting gait, and imposing size, camels have a unique beauty and movement that captured the attention of Times of Oman special correspondent Sarah MacDonald from the first time she saw them. Often referred to as the "ships of the desert", because of their ability to carry goods for long distances over the arid landscapes while surviving with very little food or water, these hardy creatures have been a major support for  many Omanis in the past. While today they are used mainly for racing, tourism, or for their agricultural benefits, they are still greatly valued and adored by those who keep them. 

Photography:  Sarah MacDonald
link_name: The many hues of the 'Ship of Desert'

A prayer for a Happy New Year - by Moign Khawaja

I wish you a happy new year,
A year without any doubts or fear,
Where you can feel successes coming near,
And on your cheeks the kisses of your dear.

A year that brings you joy and prosperity,
The days that increase your wisdom and sanity,
May you stay away from abuse and profanity,
And become the symbol of faith and vanity.

This is the time to rise and progress,
A break from the past, a careful recess,
Some hard work that ensures success,
A struggle that proves your prowess.

For this journey you may have the best of health,
To bring about revolution with all the stealth,
Generosity and kindness be part of your wealth,
With love and honesty fill the tilth.

This picture taken on December 11, 2013 shows a sand sculpture in tribute to late former South African President Nelson Mandela on Durban's beach. Mandela, the revered icon of the anti-apartheid struggle in South Africa and one of the towering political figures of the 20th century, died in Johannesburg on December 5 at age 95. Mandela, who was elected South Africa's first black president after spending nearly three decades in prison, had been receiving treatment for a lung infection at his Johannesburg home since September, after three months in hospital in a critical state.
